      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks, those are much better points. the Lockean angle is definitely something they can use to sound more sophisticated. i think they're also going to run into a lot of pushback on the \"strain on resources\" and \"wage depression\" arguments. to make sure they're fully prepared, can you walk me through how a critic would most likely try to dismantle those two specific points? i want them to see the strongest possible counter-arguments so they don't get caught off guard.",
