      "content": "Critics will argue that the \"strain on resources\" is an oversimplification, claiming that immigrants contribute significantly to the economy through consumption and filling labor gaps, thereby offsetting costs. Regarding wage depression, opponents will assert that the economic impact of immigration is overwhelmingly positive, citing increased innovation and overall GDP growth that benefits all workers. They will frame these arguments not as strains, but as necessary components of a dynamic, modern economy.",
